--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ADDITIONAL DISCLAIMER (Hardware Risk)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The Software performs low-level access to system hardware (SMBus, Super-I/O,
and SMN/PCI sensor registers) through a kernel driver. Although the driver is
deliberately narrow and applies in-kernel address allow-listing ("brick
guards") to its single bounded write path, low-level bus access carries
inherent risk to hardware. The Software is provided without warranty as stated
above; you assume all risk of running it on your hardware.
